07/04/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government is promoting a policy of zero tolerance of corruption by increasing public responsibility, according to an editorial by Romanian Prime Minister Adrian Nastase that appeared in Tuesday's (6 April) <I>Wall Street Journal</I>. 
Nastase cited a reform package passed by parliament last year aimed at combating corruption and improving the business climate. 
He also repeated his appeal to all citizens to join the fight against corruption. 
He described new reforms -- due to be completed by the end of June -- including accelerated judicial reforms and amendments to the penal and civil codes. 
(Rompres - 06/04/04)
